725640f-a.title: Queens: 75th Avenue - 164th Street
725640f-a.text:
A general view south from Seventy-fifth Ave., and 164th Street,
showing in the background the C. Eiseman farm and house from 1873 to
1891. The house is located on the line of about 167th Street.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

725641f-a.title: Queens: 75th Avenue - 164th Street
725641f-a.text:
Seventy-fifth Ave., north side (also known as Quarrelsome Lane,
also Eisemann Ave., and Hell Fire Lane), east of 164th Street (about
on the line of 167th Street), showing the L. Walters house in 1873,
and that of Henry Kiessel from 1891 to 1909. The house does not
appear in the 1928 Queens Atlas.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
